Erik Mattie, &quot;The Colours of ...: Frank O. Gehry, Jean Nouvel, Wang Shu and Other Architects&quot; 
English | ISBN: 3038213667, 3038215864 | 2015 | PDF | 376 pages | 62 MB

Colour both as aesthetic and formal medium in architecture and design is a crucial element of each building. It is treated within this book comprehensively and as it relates to practice by looking at decisive examples. The result is an account by and about three of internationally most renowned architects. It provides a compendium showing colour design within a broad horizon of technologically advanced architecture
